{
  "texts": [
    "DL techniques, as a smaller subset of ML that is also a subset of AI, have been successfully applied in the educational domain to resolve several issues, including the prediction of student's academic performance, student's learning outcomes, and early detection of students at risk of failure or dropout.",
    "DL techniques are still under development and innovative ideas are required to address these issues.",
    "These studies seek to build unique Deep Learning methodologies that help students improve their learning processes.",
    "Outline of the paper.",
    "This review is organized as follows: Section II presents and compares previous studies of both ML and DL techniques in the education field; then, the methodologies used to collect the studies that will be reviewed are described in Section III; after that, Section IV summarizes the current studies with their main idea and limitations based on the applied technique; Section V discusses DL techniques, describes the public and private datasets, and the features used in each article; Section VI presents the challenges; and finally, Section VII concludes the paper."
  ]
}